  "prompt": "Where can I learn Spanish in Delhi?",
  "response": "Delhi offers a variety of options for learning Spanish, catering to different learning styles and budgets. Here's a breakdown of some popular choices:\n\n**Formal Language Schools:**\n\n*   **Instituto Hispania:**  Considered one of the best and most established language schools in Delhi for Spanish.  They are officially recognized by the Spanish Embassy and offer a comprehensive range of courses from beginner to advanced levels. They follow the Common European Framework of Reference for Languages (CEFR). *Pros:* High quality teaching, structured curriculum, official certification, experienced instructors. *Cons:* Can be more expensive than other options.\n\n*   **Spanish Institute:** Located in various parts of Delhi.  They offer structured Spanish courses for learners of all levels, from beginners to advanced students. They focus on practical communication skills. *Pros:* Affordable, accessible locations, flexible schedules. *Cons:* Quality can vary depending on the location and instructor.\n\n**Universities and Colleges:**\n\n*   **Jawaharlal Nehru University (JNU):** Offers degree programs (BA, MA, PhD) in Spanish.  If you are looking for a long-term, academic study of the language and culture, this is a great option. *Pros:*  In-depth academic study, reputable institution. *Cons:* Requires a significant time commitment, highly competitive admissions.\n\n*   **University of Delhi (DU) - various colleges:**  Some colleges affiliated with Delhi University offer certificate or diploma courses in Spanish.  Check individual college websites for availability and details. *Pros:*  Relatively affordable, good reputation. *Cons:*  Availability depends on the college, may not be as comprehensive as a full degree program.\n\n**Private Tutors:**\n\n*   **Online Platforms (e.g., Justdial, UrbanPro):**  These platforms connect you with individual tutors in Delhi.  You can find tutors who teach online or in person, and filter by price, experience, and reviews. *Pros:*  Personalized learning, flexible schedules, can be more affordable. *Cons:*  Quality can vary greatly, requires careful vetting of tutors.\n\n**Online Learning Platforms:**\n\n*   **Duolingo:** A free, game-based app for learning basic vocabulary and grammar.  A great starting point or supplement to other methods. *Pros:* Free, fun, accessible. *Cons:* Not sufficient for advanced fluency.\n\n*   **Babbel:** A subscription-based online course that focuses on practical conversation skills.  Offers structured lessons and personalized learning. *Pros:* Convenient, affordable, focuses on practical skills. *Cons:* Requires a subscription.\n\n*   **italki:** Connects you with native Spanish speakers for online lessons and language exchange. *Pros:* Personalized instruction, learn from native speakers, flexible schedules. *Cons:* Requires payment for lessons.\n\n*   **Coursera & edX:**  Offer online Spanish courses from universities around the world.  Some courses are free, while others require a fee. *Pros:* High-quality instruction, learn from experts. *Cons:* Requires a time commitment.\n\n**Things to Consider When Choosing:**\n\n*   **Your goals:** What do you want to achieve with your Spanish?  Basic conversational skills, travel, academic study, career advancement?\n*   **Your budget:** How much are you willing to spend?\n*   **Your learning style:** Do you prefer a structured classroom setting, personalized tutoring, or self-paced online learning?\n*   **Your schedule:** How much time can you commit to learning Spanish each week?\n*   **Reputation & Reviews:** Research the language school or tutor thoroughly.  Read reviews and ask for referrals.\n*   **Accreditation:** If you need official certification, make sure the language school is accredited.\n*   **Instructor Experience & Qualifications:** Look for experienced and qualified instructors, preferably native speakers.\n\n**Recommendations:**\n\n*   **For serious learners seeking a structured and accredited program:** Instituto Hispania is highly recommended.\n*   **For budget-conscious learners:** Consider a Spanish Institute location or an online platform like Duolingo or Babbel.\n*   **For personalized instruction:** Explore private tutors on platforms like Justdial or UrbanPro.\n*   **For academic study:** Consider degree programs at JNU or certificate courses at DU colleges.\n*   **For conversation practice:** Use italki to connect with native speakers.\n\nBefore making a decision, it's best to visit the language schools, talk to instructors, and try out different learning methods to see what works best for you. Good luck!\n",
